    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-12-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.24/592</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Mexican Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Téller</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State refers to the note dated July 6, 1927, from His
                    Excellency, the Ambassador of Mexico, regarding the desire of the Mexican
                    Government to ship to Mexico certain arms and ammunition, the permission for
                    which had not been granted by the Department of State.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of State is now happy to advise the Ambassador of Mexico that
                    permission has been given to the Ward Line of New York to export to Mexico five
                    cases of guns and one case of bayonets, consigned to Jefe de Hacienda de Vera
                    Cruz, this shipment having arrived in New York from Antwerp, Belgium, on the
                    steamship <hi rend="italic">Arabic</hi>, December <pb facs="0348" n="246"
                        xml:id="pg_246"/> 27, 1926, and that E. I. duPont de Nemours and Company,
                    Incorporated, of Wilmington, Delaware, has also been authorized to export
                    twenty-five tons of powder intended for the Mexican Department of War and
                    Marine, referred to in the note of June 29, 1927, from the Secretary of State to
                    His Excellency, the Ambassador of Mexico.<note n="73" xml:id="d218fn73">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
